<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-30T11:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-30T11:45:00-05:00" n="609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.1051/403: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-30T11:00:00-05:45">May 30, 1930—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>63. Department’s instruction No. 4, April 19th. President Moncada has
                            just told me that he approves draft note with amendments as stated in my
                            air mail despatch No. 45, May 23rd, and will direct the Foreign Office
                            to submit the note.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>